articles.author: Raul Cadenas Susana Vera
articles.description: Waving Spanish flags, about 170,000 people marched through Madrid on Saturday in the largest protest yet against an amnesty law which Spain's Socialists agreed over Catalonia's 2017 separatist bid in order to form a government.
articles.title: Biggest protest in Spain against Catalan amnesty law draws 170,000

articles.author: Anne Kauranen
articles.description: Dozens of migrants stood behind barriers at two crossings on Finland's border with Russia on Saturday, the Finnish Border Guard said, after Helsinki erected barricades to halt a flow of asylum seekers it says was instigated by Moscow.
articles.title: Dozens of migrants wait at Finland-Russia border after Helsinki blocks crossings

articles.author: Carielle Doe, Alphonso Toweh
articles.description: Liberia President George Weah on Friday conceded election defeat to opposition leader Joseph Boakai after a tight race, ending a presidency marred by graft allegations but helping to ensure a smooth transition of power in the once volatile African nation.
articles.title: Liberia President George Weah concedes election defeat to Joseph Boakai

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A young Brazilian fan of U.S. singer Taylor Swift died in Rio de Janeiro on Friday night after falling ill inside the sweltering stadium where the superstar's concert was held, amid a record-breaking heat-wave across large swathes of Brazil.
articles.title: Fan dies at Taylor Swift show in sweltering Rio de Janeiro

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Igor Girkin, a prominent ultranationalist in custody in Russia awaiting trial on charges of inciting extremism, nominated himself to run for president in 2024 in an announcement read on his behalf on Saturday, the online SOTA news channel said.
articles.title: Jailed Russian nationalist nominates himself for president

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: At least 300 people protested in El Salvador on Saturday against an anti-gang crackdown they said was putting innocent people behind bars, hours before the Central American country hosts the Miss Universe competition for the first time since 1975.
articles.title: El Salvador hosts Miss Universe as protesters denounce mass arrests

articles.author: Special Reports
articles.description: At a Gaza hospital, a midwife brings new life and volunteers tend to the dead
articles.title: At a Gaza hospital, a midwife brings life and volunteers tend the dead

articles.author: Maggie Fick
articles.description: John, a tech executive who has been battling weight gain since his 30s, has a nine-month supply in his refrigerator. Kim Gradwell, a retired receptionist who developed type 2 diabetes nearly 20 years ago, isn't sure where she'll find her next dose.
articles.title: How well-off Brits still buy Ozempic online for weight loss

articles.author: Sarah Marsh, Andreas Rinke
articles.description: Leaders from more than a dozen African countries are heading to Germany for the G20 Compact with Africa conference, which aims to help bolster private investment in the world's poorest, but fast-growing, continent.
articles.title: G20-led summit for Africa highlights renewed interest in fast-growing continent
